Defendant Melissa A Pallagi in court with attorney Kirk Andrew Redetzke.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Statement by defendant's employer, brother and father.

Plea Colloquy.

Court will not accept a not contest plea.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read in. 

The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld Sentence of:
(Credit - 1 day) if revoked

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of  illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of probation to be performed in a drug rehabilitation center and to be completed in the 10th month of the second year of probation;
- Maintain a valid Driver's License;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Court suggests the agent and defendant to review is NA  is appropriate;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To be paid at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing 10-1-15)  

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.  

Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal cases pending.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
